        Leafwhisper agreed, "Exactly! The bureaucratic procedures were clearly designed for beings who don't naturally coordinate through shared networks, so applying them literally to us was unnecessarily redundant, but the underlying concepts about individual needs and identity were genuinely useful —"

        Rootwalker broke in suddenly, "Question."

        They'd reached another rest stop. I haven't even noticed the kilometers passing — my body has found the rhythm.

        I sit gratefully anyway.

        Scout rolled over immediately, settling against my leg. The little plant was learning rest stop patterns too.
