        I say quietly, "I miss trees — back home. But they weren't like this. They were just trees, individual plants competing for light and water."

        Rootwalker observed, "Lonely way to live."

        Leafwhisper said, "It must have been! Though Earth forests did have fungal networks too. Early human researchers just didn't recognize the communication happening underground — they thought of trees as isolated entities when really they were sharing resources and information all along, just without individual language to make it obvious."

