        They walked.

        The afternoon passed in questions and answers — Leafwhisper explaining plant-society structures, territorial networks, how different species contributed different capabilities, why some plants stayed rooted while others developed mobility, what it felt like to photosynthesize, whether mushrooms counted as plants or their own category.

        Rootwalker contributed occasional one-word clarifications or corrections.

        Scout continued exploring, bringing back chemical signatures from interesting discoveries.

        And I walk, learning to see the forest not as backdrop but as society — complex, interconnected, beautiful.

